<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6629274-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3307"><num value="3307">§ 3307.</num><heading> Frequency of inspection</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each vessel subject to inspection under this part shall undergo an initial inspection for certification before being put into service. After being put into service—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6629275-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3307/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> each passenger vessel, nautical school vessel, and small passenger vessel allowed to carry more than 12 passengers on a foreign voyage shall be inspected at least once a year; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6629276-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3307/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> any other vessel shall be inspected at least once every 5 years.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf6629277-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/514">97 Stat. 514</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/104/324/tVI/s605/a">Pub. L. 104–324, title VI, § 605(a)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-19">Oct. 19, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3931">110 Stat. 3931</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf6629278-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
